	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />koitsu graciously allowed me to give a home to a broken FDS. Not having a Famicom myself, i was wondering if the following is possible: 
<br />
<br />  1. Acquire ca. 1985 gyromite/hogan's alley with internal FC-&gt;NES converter
<br />  2. Plug FDS "RAM" module into said converter
<br />  3. Plug converter into NTSC top-loading NES
<br />
<br />I haven't really seen this discussed anywhere, but i see no reason why this should not work. With the exception of external sound hardware not being available, of course.
<br />
<br />Or should i just try and locate an A/V Famicom?
<br />
<br />Thanks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
